20/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Visiting Bucharest on Wednesday (19 November), Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano said Albania and Romania share the same Euro-Atlantic integration ambitions and would seek further co-operation in a variety of areas. For his part, Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase assured him that Albanian companies are welcome to come to Romania and do business. The sides also agreed that regional co-operation is required to fight organised crime and trafficking
In other news, Tirana Police Chief Pjerin Ndreu wrote an open letter Wednesday, warning that organised crime is becoming a threat to democracy. He cited several high-profile assassinations in recent months. (Rompres, ATA, Albanian Daily News, AFP - 19/11/03)
